Head. Ommatidia absent. Postantennal organ (PAO) narrow, 0.68–0.74 times as width of Ant. I base, without inner denticles, with 6 guard setae (
Fig. 1
). Labral setal formula as 4 / 5, 5 , 4 (
Fig. 2
). Labium with 4 + 4 basomedian setae, 3 + 3 proximal setae, 5 + 5 basolateral and 4 + 4 postlabial setae (
Fig. 3
). Ant. I with 2 dorsal basal microsensilla (ms) and 2 ventral sensilla (s), one s larger and more translucent. Ant. II with 1 dorsal, 1 ventral and 1 lateral basal ms and 1 apical lateral translucent s. Ant. III with 1 basal ms and 1 lateral s; antennal organ ( AO ) consisting of 2 inner s, 2 outer s, inner ones finger-like (
Figs 4
a, b). Except common setae, Ant. IV with 39–46 s of different sizes, all translucent, 6 of them apparently thicker than others (
Figs 5
). Sensilla thinnerwalled and translucent usually slender than common setae.

Body chaetotaxy. Macroseta (Mac) larger than common seta. Sensillum (s) slightly shorter, more translucent and slender than common seta (c). Microsensillum (ms) thick-walled and smaller than s. Mac formula as 1, 1 / 3, 3 , 3, 4 ; largest ones on last 3 abdominal segments 3.4-4.0 times as length of mucro. Sensillar formulae as 4, 3 / 2, 2 , 2, 3 (s) and 1 , 0 / 0, 0, 0 (ms) (
Fig. 6
). Sensilla probably present on Abd.V, but hardly distinguishable. Medial s on Th. II–Abd. III well in front of posterior row of dorsal setae (p-row); those on Abd. I–III situated between Mac 1 and Mac 2 , and much closer to Mac 2 . Corner sensillum (cors) located in p-row on Th. II–III (
Fig. 7
). Lateral sensillum located in p-row on Abd. I and in front of p-row on Abd. II–III (
Figs. 8 & 9
). The leaf-shaped sensilla on Abd. IV–VI are absent. Common setae along median line on each side (Axial setae–ax) of Th. II–Abd. III as 9, 7 ( 6 ) / 4, 4 , 4 . Thorax without ventral setae.

Appendages. Unguis and unguiculus toothless. Tibiotarsal setae arranged in 3 rings, each with 7 setae on leg I–II (
Figs 10, 11
); and 25–28 setae on leg III probably in 4 rings (
Fig. 12
). Ventral tube with 4 + 4 laterodistal (
Fig. 13
) and 6 posterior setae. Retinaculum with 4 teeth on each ramus and 1 seta on corpus (
Fig. 14
). Anterior and posterior parts of furcal subcoxa respectively with 5–6 and 3 setae (
Fig. 15
). Manubrium anteriorly with 3 + 3 setae in 2 longitudinal rows (
Fig. 16
); posteriorly with 4 + 4 latero-basal, 3 + 3 central, 2 + 2 distal, and 1 + 1 apical (
Fig. 17
); laterally with 1 + 1 setae (
Fig. 16
). Dens anteriorly with 10–11 , posteriorly with 2 basal and 2 medial setae (
Figs 16, 17
). Mucro with 2 teeth, subapical one larger than apical (
Figs 16, 17
). Length ratio of manubrium: dens: mucro as 5.4-6.9:6.3-7.1: 1 .
